<TITLE> EC ready to stretch party constitution deadline </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 5 (bdnews24.com)The Election Commission was open to the suggestion of giving political parties more time beyond the latest July 25 deadline to submit a permanent constitution, commissioner Muhammad Sohul Hossain said on Sunday. "We have no problem increasing the deadline. But we need written [applications from political parties] for that," he told reporters at the EC secretariat. "We will make a decision after getting [written applications]," he added. Ruling Awami League has decided to seek another six months, while the main opposition BNP hinted that they might also seek more time. Hossain reminded the parties that submitting permanent constitution was a must under the new electoral law for registration, without which no party can take part in the polls. Many parties sought time on the grounds that they needed time to fulfil the conditions for registration. They had promised before the ninth parliamentary election to amend their constitutions through councils. The commission registered the parties going by their draft constitutions. bd
